I’ve got a few item available that will be hitting the website soon. Hammers, axes, bottle openers, tea light candle holders and center punches. I’ll also be adding a few more things in the next week or two and they can all make for great Christmas gifts😉 if you interested in anything feel free to shoot me a dm or go checkout the website link in my bio.

Forging a head progression to add to my collection. It always feels difficult to squeeze the relevant info into a short video but I did my best. This is a fun project that can be done with relatively basic tools. Hope this inspires others to try it! If you have questions or ideas for other progressions feel free to drop them in the comments👌🏻

I think I’ll have to call this the bullet ball peen. I really like the clean simple transitions although not so simple to make it look the way I wanted😜 I’ve got 2 of these 28oz hammers up on the site along with some dog heads, cross peens and some other items. Check it out if you’re interested and as always feel free to dm me if you have any questions. Have a great weekend.

Using the induction heater to make a set of bamboo vessels out of 16g 2-1/4” pipe. I’d like to see how large of a diameter I can get this unit to heat at some point🧐 the 2 loop coil worked a lot better than 3 but the machine acts very strange on this larger diameter pipe.

The new Guillotines are coming along nicely. A fresh batch is just about ready to go and we will reach out to everyone who has been patiently waiting. If you’re interested in one don’t hesitate to send us a message with any questions. We built these to last a lifetime and they are a game changer even if you have a forging press and power hammer.

I’ve been welding for a while and have always kind of hated the gun holders that seem to be generally the same. They pick up junk and the magnet breaks away very easily. I decided to experiment and modify one to have an on/off base and I’m liking it already. Room for improvement of course but at least it’s easy to clean off and move around. Would love to know what you think. Feel free to send it to the big companies so they can make something better.😉

I’ve never posted anything about my personal life on here or even pictures of myself really but this felt like something I had to share. @kateydolezal and I just had our first baby girl Ember Rose and it’s just been a mind blowing experience, in a good way. I’ve become friends with so many people through this platform and the maker community but it’s hard to reach out to everyone to tell them the news, especially now. I can’t wait for her to join the community 🙂if she wants to haha

An anvil is born. It has been a while since @sunsetforgenj and I have forged one of these. Perhaps this will be one of our demos at this years @themakercamp 🧐 what would you like to see us make? Hope to see you there, it’s always a tremendously fun event with a lot of great people and talented makers👌🏻

Soldering and testing this new 1/2” ID induction coil I got from @cluaranforge it works like a charm👌🏻 the test pieces were 5/32”, 1/4” and 3/8” it had the 3/8” round bar at melting temp in under 10 seconds.

Do you want it? 2-1/4lb diamond face cross peen ready to go soon. Lot of other cool stuff on the website that can still be shipped out in time for Christmas! Thanks for taking a look and if you need it dm me 🌲

This 2lb farrier style rounding hammer would make a nice stocking stuffer I think🙂 lots of good stuff available on the website in my bio. Today’s the last day I can pack anything up to get out in time for Xmas. If you’re interested in knowing when new stuff is available head over to the site and subscribe, we promise we won’t send thousands of emails 👍🏼😎🌲
